title: Executive Order 7392-Revocation of Executive Order No. 6014 of February 6, 1933, Withdrawing Public Lands in Oregon
content: By virtue of and pursuant to the authority vested in me by the act of June 25, 1910, ch. 421, 36 Stat. 847, as amended by the act of August 24, 1912, ch. 369, 37 Stat. 497, Executive Order No. 6014 of February 6, 1933, withdrawing public lands in T. 17 S., R. 9 W. of the Willamette meridian, Oregon, pending a resurvey, is hereby revoked.
This order shall become effective upon the date of the official filing of the plat of resurvey of said township.
citation: Franklin D. Roosevelt, Executive Order 7392-Revocation of Executive Order No. 6014 of February 6, 1933, Withdrawing Public Lands in Oregon Online by Gerhard Peters and John T. Woolley, The American Presidency Project https://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/node/355775
